      • uiReadySinglePaymentCheck

        public static CheckBuilder uiReadySinglePaymentCheck(ReserveLine reserveLine,
                                                     CurrencyAmount amount)
        Returns a CheckBuilder to create a single check in a checkset, with one payment. The payment will: have a single line item with the specified amount, erode reserves, have the currency of amount if non-null, or otherwise of the claim, be of partial payment type, be in AWAITINGSUBMISSION state. The payment details cannot be modified in the builder, though they can be changed after the entity has been created. The check will: have one payee (its reserveline's claim's insured), have a check number of "1234", have an invoice number of "123456789", be of primary check type, have a scheduled send date of today, be in AWAITINGSUBMISSION state. This method requires an already-created reserveline. The check created using this builder will not go through any approval rules, and can be committed even if it exceeds reserves (creating offsetting reserves in the process). For building checks with multiple payments, it may be more appropriate to use CheckBuilder.uiReadyCheckWithoutPaymentOrCheckSet(claim).
        Parameters:
        reserveLine - the reserveline the payment on the created check should be coded to
        amount - the amount of the (single) payment on the created check
        Returns:
        ui-ready checkbuilder with default values typically selected through a run of the check wizard.

      • uiReadySinglePaymentCheck

        public static CheckBuilder uiReadySinglePaymentCheck(ReserveLine reserveLine,
                                                     CurrencyAmount amount,
                                                     Currency currency)
        Returns a CheckBuilder to create a single check in a checkset, with one payment. The payment will: have a single line item with the specified amount, have the specified currency, erode reserves, be of partial payment type, be in AWAITINGSUBMISSION state. The payment details cannot be modified in the builder, though they can be changed after the entity has been created. The check will: have one payee (its reserveline's claim's insured), have a check number of "1234", have an invoice number of "123456789", be of primary check type, have a scheduled send date of today, be in AWAITINGSUBMISSION state. This method requires an already-created reserveline. The check created using this builder will not go through any approval rules, and can be committed even if it exceeds reserves (creating offsetting reserves in the process). For building checks with multiple payments, it may be more appropriate to use CheckBuilder.uiReadyCheckWithoutPaymentOrCheckSet(claim).

      • uiReadySinglePaymentCheck

        public static CheckBuilder uiReadySinglePaymentCheck(CurrencyAmount amount,
                                                     TransactionStatus checkStatus,
                                                     TransactionStatus paymentStatus)
        Commits a new claim and claim-level reserve to the database, then returns a CheckBuilder to create a single check in a checkset, with one payment, on the new claim. The payment will: be on the same reserve line as the reserve, have a single line item with the specified amount, have the currency of the specified amount, erode reserves, be of partial payment type, have the specified TransactionStatus. The payment details cannot be modified in the builder, though they can be changed after the entity has been created. The check will: have one payee (its reserve line's claim's insured), have a check number of "1234", have an invoice number of "123456789", be of primary check type, have a scheduled send date of today, have the specified TransactionStatus. Note: Because it performs a commit, this method cannot be used from a test that expects to be able to save the contents of the bundle to staging tables. The check created using this builder will not go through any approval rules. For building checks with multiple payments, it may be more appropriate to use CheckBuilder.uiReadyCheckWithoutPaymentOrCheckSet(claim).
        Parameters:
        amount - the amount of the (single) payment on the created check
        checkStatus - the status of the created check
        paymentStatus - the status of the (single) payment on the created check
        Returns:
        ui-ready checkbuilder with default values typically selected through a run of the check wizard.

      • uiReadySinglePaymentCheck

        public static CheckBuilder uiReadySinglePaymentCheck(Claim claim,
                                                     CurrencyAmount amount,
                                                     TransactionStatus checkStatus,
                                                     TransactionStatus paymentStatus)
        Commits the passed in claim and a new claim-level reserve to the database, then returns a CheckBuilder to create a single check in a checkset, with one payment, on the new claim. The payment will: be on the same reserve line as the reserve, have a single line item with the specified amount, have the currency of the specified amount, erode reserves, be of partial payment type, have the specified TransactionStatus. The payment details cannot be modified in the builder, though they can be changed after the entity has been created. The check will: have one payee (its reserve line's claim's insured), have a check number of "1234", have an invoice number of "123456789", be of primary check type, have a scheduled send date of today, have the specified TransactionStatus. Note: Because it performs a commit, this method cannot be used from a test that expects to be able to save the contents of the bundle to staging tables. The check created using this builder will not go through any approval rules. For building checks with multiple payments, it may be more appropriate to use CheckBuilder.uiReadyCheckWithoutPaymentOrCheckSet(claim).
        Parameters:
        amount - the amount of the (single) payment on the created check
        checkStatus - the status of the created check
        paymentStatus - the status of the (single) payment on the created check
        Returns:
        ui-ready checkbuilder with default values typically selected through a run of the check wizard.

      • uiReadySinglePaymentCheck

        public static CheckBuilder uiReadySinglePaymentCheck(ReserveLine reserveLine,
                                                     CurrencyAmount amount,
                                                     Currency currency,
                                                     TransactionStatus checkStatus,
                                                     TransactionStatus paymentStatus,
                                                     PaymentType paymentType,
                                                     boolean erodesReserves)
        Returns a CheckBuilder to create a single check in a checkset, with one payment. The payment will: have a single line item with the specified amount, have the specified currency, erode reserves, be of partial payment type, have the specified TransactionStatus. The payment details cannot be modified in the builder, though they can be changed after the entity has been created. The check will: have one payee (its reserveline's claim's insured), have a check number of "1234", have an invoice number of "123456789", be of primary check type, have a scheduled send date of today have the specified TransactionStatus. This method requires an already-created reserveline.       • uiReadyCheckWithoutPaymentOrCheckSet

        public static CheckBuilder uiReadyCheckWithoutPaymentOrCheckSet(Claim claim)
        Returns a checkbuilder that will create a check with no payments or checkset. The caller of this method is expected to explicitly add payments, using either withPayment(PaymentBuilder) or payment.onCheck(Check). The check will: be on the specified claim, have its check number and invoice number populated, have AwaitingSubmission status, have its issue date, date of service, servicePdStart, and servicePdEnd populated with today's date, have its payee and related fields set up with the claim's insured, and have a scheduled send date of today.
        Parameters:
        claim - the claim that this check is linked to
        Returns:
        checkbuilder with minimal fields set and no payments
